      • readConfigurationFile

        public static java.util.ArrayList<AggConfigElements> readConfigurationFile()
                                                                    throws java.io.IOException
        readConfigurationFile() reads aggregation configurations by:
        1. Reading collectd.conf file, capture aggregation section, and saves it into an object of AggConfigElements. The object has the following keys and values:
        - Fault Tolerance Time Window: the time period in seconds that allows the nodes of the under monitoring system to send the metric data to Observability, so the aggregator can have as much data possible to perform the aggregation. If no value is provided or if it is not a valid number, use the default value.
        - Aggregation interval: the time in seconds that Observability aggregates the data and writes them to DB. If no value is provided or if it is not a valid number, use the default value.
        - Metric to aggregate: captured from "plugin" key element of collectd.conf file.
        - Type of metric to aggregate: captured from "typeInstance" key element of collectd.conf file.
        - Aggregation function to apply: captured from the status of the relative key elements of collectd.conf file
        Returns:
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        NotBoundException
